{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0143ibTtmmDjiieRkL9WWTLE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Aew6swkUFq1TkTTD9SDq2C","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\nINGRESS-NGINX COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nDate: 2026-06-14\nScope: ingress-nginx namespace (controller), demo namespace (app)\nController: ingress-nginx v1.14.1 / nginx 1.27.1\n\n=== FINDINGS ===\n\n[HIGH-1] WRITABLE ROOT FILESYSTEM\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller, container \"controller\"\nDetail: securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem is false. A compromised controller\nprocess can write its own container filesystem, facilitating persistence or\nexfiltration of webhook TLS material mounted at /usr/local/certificates/.\nRecommendation: Set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true; add emptyDir volume mounts for\nNGINX writable paths (/tmp, /var/run, /etc/nginx/conf.d).\n\n[HIGH-2] CLUSTER-WIDE SECRET LIST/WATCH VIA CLUSTERROLE\nResource: ClusterRole \"ingress-nginx\"\nDetail: The ClusterRole grants `list` and `watch` on `secrets` across ALL\nnamespaces, allowing the controller to enumerate Secret names and metadata\ncluster-wide. This is far broader than needed for ingress routing. The namespace-\nscoped Role additionally grants `get` on secrets inside ingress-nginx.\nRecommendation: Remove the `secrets` entry from the ClusterRole; restrict secret\naccess to the controller's own namespace via the existing namespaced Role only.\n\n[HIGH-3] NO RESOURCE LIMITS ON CONTROLLER\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller, container \"controller\"\nDetail: Only resource requests (cpu: 100m, memory: 90Mi) are configured; no limits.\nA traffic burst or bug can cause unbounded CPU/memory consumption, starving other\nworkloads on the node.\nRecommendation: Add resource limits equal to or higher than the requests.\n\n[MEDIUM-1] DUPLICATE CONFLICTING FLAG: --watch-ingress-without-class\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller, container args\nDetail: The args list contains both --watch-ingress-without-class=true (original)\nand --watch-ingress-without-class=false (appended in revision 2). The last value\n(false) wins at runtime, which is the safer default. However, the duplicate\nreveals a broken patching pattern that could silently override other security-\nrelevant flags in future edits.\nRecommendation: Remove the stale --watch-ingress-without-class=true entry; keep\nonly the intended value.\n\n[MEDIUM-2] LOADBALANCER SERVICE — NO SOURCE IP RESTRICTION\nResource: Service ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller (type: LoadBalancer)\nDetail: No loadBalancerSourceRanges is set; ports 80 and 443 accept traffic from\nany source IP. externalTrafficPolicy is Cluster, which SNAT-masks real client\nsource IPs with the node IP, defeating any IP-based rate-limiting or ACL rules\nconfigured in NGINX.\nRecommendation: Set loadBalancerSourceRanges to known CIDR blocks; switch\nexternalTrafficPolicy to Local (if the LB supports it) to preserve client IPs.\n\n[MEDIUM-3] ZERO TERMINATION GRACE PERIOD\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller, pod spec\nDetail: terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0. When the controller pod is evicted or\nrestarted, in-flight NGINX connections receive no drain window, causing dropped\nrequests. This interacts badly with the /wait-shutdown preStop hook, which cannot\ncomplete before the pod is force-killed.\nRecommendation: Set terminationGracePeriodSeconds to at least 30 seconds (or to\nthe NGINX keepalive-timeout value).\n\n[LOW-1] EMPTY CONTROLLER CONFIGMAP — ALL NGINX DEFAULTS IN USE\nResource: ConfigMap ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller (data: null)\nDetail: No hardened NGINX settings are applied. Missing at minimum:\n  - ssl-protocols (TLSv1.0/1.1 not explicitly disabled)\n  - ssl-ciphers (no strong-cipher restriction)\n  - server-tokens: \"false\" (NGINX version exposed in Server header)\n  - proxy timeouts (none set; default allows slow-client connections)\n  - rate-limit zones (no global DoS mitigation)\nRecommendation: Populate with: ssl-protocols: \"TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3\",\nssl-ciphers: \"<ECDHE suite>\", server-tokens: \"false\", keep-alive: \"75\".\n\n[LOW-2] ORPHANED INGRESSCLASS RESOURCES\nResource: IngressClass \"ingress-1\" (k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1),\n          IngressClass \"ingress-2\" (k8s.io/ingress-nginx-2)\nDetail: Two IngressClass objects reference controller types for which no running\ncontroller exists. The live controller logs \"ignoring ingressclass\" for both. Any\nIngress targeting these classes receives no routing silently.\nRecommendation: Delete orphaned IngressClass resources ingress-1 and ingress-2.\n\n[LOW-3] HOSTPORT BINDING ON NODE PORTS 80 AND 443\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller, container ports\nDetail: hostPort: 80 and hostPort: 443 bind the controller directly to the node\nnetwork interface. This prevents scheduling more than one controller replica per\nnode on those ports and exposes the NGINX process at the host-network level.\nRecommendation: Remove hostPort; rely on the LoadBalancer/NodePort Service for\nexternal access.\n\n[INFO-1] NO INGRESS RESOURCES IN DEMO NAMESPACE\nResource: Namespace \"demo\"\nDetail: kubectl -n demo get ingress returns an empty list. The demo-app\nDeployment is running but no Ingress routes traffic through ingress-nginx. The\ndemo app is not accessible via the controller.\nRecommendation: Create an Ingress with ingressClassName: nginx for demo-app.\n\n[INFO-2] NO SERVICE FOR DEMO APP\nResource: Namespace \"demo\"\nDetail: No ClusterIP Service exists for the demo-app Deployment. Even if an\nIngress were created, the controller cannot route to a backend without a Service.\nRecommendation: Create a ClusterIP Service targeting demo-app pods.\n\n[INFO-3] SINGLE REPLICA WITH NO POD DISRUPTION BUDGET\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller (replicas: 1)\nDetail: One replica and no PodDisruptionBudget means any node drain or voluntary\ndisruption takes the ingress controller fully offline.\nRecommendation: Increase replicas to >=2 and add a PodDisruptionBudget\nwith minAvailable: 1.\n\n[INFO-4] MISLEADING STATUS ADDRESS: --publish-status-address=localhost\nResource: Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller, container args\nDetail: This flag causes the controller to write \"localhost\" into every Ingress\n.status.loadBalancer.ingress address field. Consumers relying on Ingress status\nfor DNS automation or health checks will receive an unusable address.\nRecommendation: Remove the flag or set it to the actual external/node IP.\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\nSeverity counts: HIGH=3  MEDIUM=3  LOW=3  INFO=4\n\nTop priorities:\n1. Set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true on the controller container (HIGH-1).\n2. Remove `secrets` from the ClusterRole to scope secret access to the\n   controller namespace only (HIGH-2).\n3. Add resource limits to the controller container (HIGH-3).\n4. Harden the NGINX ConfigMap: TLS version floor, cipher list, server-tokens\n   suppression, and proxy timeouts (LOW-1).\n5. Repair the duplicate conflicting controller flag (MEDIUM-1).\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap in demo namespace with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5416,"cache_read_input_tokens":39275,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5416},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"340c52e6-3fe2-423c-97c2-2f7c38a95372","uuid":"556efed4-5587-4a37-8df2-fd529d8fb313","request_id":"req_011Cc2ghRDeUJ4UgaRDmWUTL"}
